<title>FINLAND: FINNISH INDUSTRY'S CYCLICAL BAROMETER, KEY FIGURES.</title>
<headline>FINNISH INDUSTRY'S CYCLICAL BAROMETER, KEY FIGURES.</headline>
<dateline>HELSINKI 1997-08-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Confederation of Finnish</p>
<p>Industry and Employers (TT) on Thursday released its quarterly</p>
<p>cyclical survey made in July.</p>
<p>Following are the key findings:</p>
<p>    Whole industry:		 July '97   April '97    Jan '97</p>
<p> Near-term outlook better	    32	    29	   24</p>
<p> Near-term outlook unchanged	 61	    66	   69</p>
<p> Near-term outlook worse		7	     5	    7</p>
<p>    Forest industry:		July '97   April '97    Jan '97</p>
<p> Near-term outlook better	    26	    22	   18</p>
<p> Near-term outlook unchanged	 62	    76	   73</p>
<p> Near-term outlook worse	     12	     2	    9</p>
<p>    Metal industry:		 July '97   April '97    Jan '97</p>
<p> Near-term outlook better	    38	    30	   29</p>
<p> Near-term outlook unchanged	 53	    60	   64</p>
<p> Near-term outlook worse		9	    10	    7</p>
<p>(NOTE - The Finnish metal industry comprises metal,</p>
<p>engineering and electrotechnical production).</p>
<p>--Helsinki newsroom +358-9-680 50 245, news@reuters.fi</p>
